&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Cardiothoracic Directorate provides high quality emergency, secondary, regional and national specialist services in Cardiology, Cardiac and Thoracic surgery. This role is pivotal in enabling the Directorate to provide a high-quality, comprehensive and professional administrative service to patients, relatives, carers and other internal and external stakeholders&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited from individuals with excellent secretarial and administrative skills who look forward to working within a busy and challenging environment. You will be able to provide evidence of exceptional organisational skills, as well as an understanding of patient pathways and patient care/experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have excellent computer, audio and keyboard skills along with the ability to prioritise their own workload, have the ability to communicate effectively using a variety of media and have an appreciation of the need for confidentiality at all times. This post will require working at predominantly the Royal Hallamshire, but will also be expected to work at the Northern General on occasions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameFrancesca PassaseoTelephone number0114 2714341&lt;/p&gt;
